Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 60 MONTHS, with credit for 7 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 24 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 36 MONTHS.  

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 36 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) Court ordered 10 MONTHS of condition time in the House of Correction, FORTHWITH. Defendant to have release for programming/treatment he is currently receiving at the VA;
2) Pay all costs, fees, surcharges, and fines during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
3) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
4) No driving;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety;
6) Random urine screens;
7) 24 month Ignition Interlock;
8) Pay a fine of $600.00;
9) 24 months driver's license revocation;

Court ordered bail on deposit to apply. 

If revoked, defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

If revoked, court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/earnings.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
